          For the purpose of this investigation, we looked at the <i>event</i> of Bihar
          Elections. Mediatically, Elections are mega events giving us a good anchor point for this investigation. 
          <br> <br>
          Since 2014, elections in India, USA and most other places are being fought in the digital space. Perception management, PR, misinformation, rumors, gossip, affect, emotion and the production of rift are some of the methods used for campaigning, as they have always been. But now algorithmicaly computability of emotion became our subject. The rules are old, methods are tested but the tools of deployment at scale bring us to the meat of the matter - How to counter-deploy? What are the counter architectures ? 
          <br> <br>

          The collapse of the entire journalistic body in India begs the very basic question - What is fake news, what is misinformation and what is relatively real news? Are there any parameters for this anymore ? The new ecosystem has collapsed ads, propoganda, and deepfakes into a single stream that can never be stepped in twice. What does this change on the ground ? This was the question.

