        <h1>4. 'user' is a political category </h1>

        <p>

        The next observation is about the category of the user - Currently the user
        has no rights. The user can only agree to the terms and conditions to
        participate in the online life.
        The user is forbidden from being political. Various tactics of aesthetic
        mediation, shadow banning, warning, intimidation and denial are used.
        <br><br>

        The <i>user</i> is the labor, the resource and the product. The citizen, the actor, the mask, the historical body, the consumer, the voter,
        the influencer, the hacker, the bureaucrat, the pirate and the coder - the
        singular in the public, different from singular in the data. How the production
        of desire affects positions and perspectives ?
        What tools do we as users need to assert our political rights as users ?
        What differentiates the phantom publics of Nepal from the sit in publics of
        Occupy movement?
        What is it that doesn‚Äôt make the user ask for more than the ability to like share
        and subscribe?
        How is it that the users can identify - isolation, depression, provide new
        vocabularies, but not question their positions as users in the isolationist
        tech ?<br><br>
        The social media billionaire is an old category - the new category is the ai
        billionaire. This points to a future where ai consumes the data produced by
        the user and regurgitates it into new configurations of the voice, personae,
        body, ‚Äòlinguistic thought‚Äô and even a public. The voice without a body, a body
        without a voice, and a body with thought. The scope of influence that we as
        individuals have on each other is immense. There is an immense potential in
        conversation.
        What is the scope of phantom conversations ? A phantom public made real
        and real made phantom in the image of each other. This has profound
        political consequences that are worth considering.
        <br><br>
        
